# Polynomial Regression

In math, we say that the **basis** of power functions is the set

$$\{ 1, x, x^{2}, x^{3}, x^{4}, ...\}$$

and we can expand regression models as

$$y = a + bx + cx^{2} + dx^{3} + ...$$

or

$$y = \beta_{0} + \beta_{1}x + \beta_{2}x^{2} + \beta_{3}x^{3} + ...$$


