# Exponential Regression

$$\begin{array}{rcl}
y & = & A(B^{x}) \\
\ln y & = & \ln A(B^{x}) \\
\ln y & = & \ln A + x\ln B \\
\end{array}$$

* response variable: log(`damage`)
* $\beta_0 = \ln A$ and $\beta_{1} = \ln B$



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exp_fit <- lm(log(damage) ~ year, data = hurricane_df)
exp_fit
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

